			<div class="card click" data-direction="left">
				  
          <div class="front Event"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://www.valleylibrary.ca/sites/default/files/styles/featured_event/public/event_images/wood%20turtle.JPG?itok=opr0Acpt" width="140" height="140" alt="" /><h3 class="featured-event-location">Lawrencetown - Dr. Frank W. Morse Memorial Library</h3><h2 class="featured-event-title">Community Wood Turtle Stewardship Meeting</h2></div>    
          <div class="back Event"><div class="featured-events-back-wrapper"><h3 class="featured-event-location">Lawrencetown - Dr. Frank W. Morse Memorial Library</h3><h2 class="featured-event-title">Community Wood Turtle Stewardship Meeting</h2><h4 class="featured-event-date"><div class="featured-event-day"><span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2016-09-13T19:00:00-03:00">September 13th (Tue)</span></div><div class="featured-event-time"><span class="date-display-single"><span class="date-display-start" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2016-09-13T19:00:00-03:00">7:00pm</span> to <span class="date-display-end" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2016-09-13T20:30:00-03:00">8:30pm</span></span></div></h4><p class="featured-event-info">The wood turtle is a species at risk that has a confirmed habitat in the village of Lawrencetown. CARP will explain the voluntary stewardship program and how to become a wood turtle friendly community.  Learn how to protect our wildlife habitat. If you are a land owner, manager or user,  we hope to see you there.
</p></div><a href="/event/community-wood-turtle-stewardship-meeting" class="featured-event-link">Learn More <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a></div>  			</div>
